<a name="Revising Tests">
<h4>
2.2.3.  Revising Tests and Editing Settings
</h4>
</a>
<p>
To revise a test, the user selects <tt>Edit</tt> as shown in Figure 2-6.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Filled Test">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/gen-test-filled.png" style="height:50%">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2-6: Filled Test </p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>
To edit or remove a question, the user selects ellipses <tt>...</tt> as shown in Figure 2-7, and then <tt>Edit</tt> or <tt>Remove</tt> as shown in Figure 2-8.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Filled Test Mid Edit">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/gen-test-filled-edit.png" style="height:50%">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2-7: Filled Test Mid Edit</p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Edit or Remove">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/gen-test-edit-remove.png" style="height:10%">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2-8: Edit or Remove</p>
<hr>
</a>
<br>

<p>
To save the test, the user selects <tt>Save</tt>. To go back to the home screen, the user selects <tt>Back</tt> as shown in Figure 2-7. A dialogue will pop up as shown in Figure 2-9, prompting the user to save before exiting. Options are <tt>Don't Save</tt>, <tt>Cancel</tt>, or <tt>Save</tt>.
<br>
<br>
<hr>
<a name="Exit Without Saving?">
<p align=center>
<img src="images/gen-test-exit-warning.png" style="height:20%">
</p>
<p align=center> Figure 2-9: Exit Without Saving?</p>
<hr>
</a>
